node.text: Great times with everyone at @bootlegcanyonmtbpark last week! This particular trail always feels more like an enduro race on a downhill bike which is both fun and not fun in ways haha. Good to be back on track, can’t wait for the races to pick back up these next few months. Thanks to Mike and the staff for the hard work and fun weekend. 💪🏼👊🏼 @gopro #hero9black @intensecycles

node.text: Hey guys, a little injury update. I’ve been doin everything I can to get my back healed up since my crash. I’m making good progress for such a short amount of time but still a little ways out from being at 100% or even able to ride. That said I won’t be racing at Worlds next week but am still hoping to be back for the last few World Cups. This injury has been a tough one timing wise but I’m feelin very positive and excited for the future. I’ll keep workin hard and I’m confident that I’ll get back to where I want to be. Thanks everyone for the kind messages lately and I’d like to say a huge good luck to team USA next week! Can’t wait to get back and represent at world’s next year, we’ve got some work to do at that race! 🇺🇸💪🏼👊🏼 📷 @kgcontent

node.text: Can’t believe it’s already been a year! It’s so much fun being married to you. Thanks babe for all your love and all you do. Can’t imagine things any different now, life is truly great with you by my side. Now get out of bed, I’m hungry, gonna make pancakes, and you’re taking forever. 😂🥞 I love you!!! 😘 @swannyberg

node.text: That new @thormxofficial race kit was lookin 🔥🔥 last weekend. We’ve been kinda flyin under the radar with this deal while we develop the new gear but man I’m stoked on this! Rode Thor gear as a kid racing Moto and it’s crazy to be the dude bringing them into the MTB scene now. Exciting things to come. 😎 #braaap
